
===================================
📌 1. Finglish Version (Persian Latin Script)
===================================

📖 **Tashrih:**
    Dastoor `neqn` yek dastoor baraye hesabe riyazi dar terminal ast. Ba estefade az in dastoor, shoma mitavanid mohasebate sade ra anjam dahid.

⚙️ **Gozine-ha:**
    🔹 `neqn 'expression'` --> ➕ Hesab kardane expression riyazi. Expression bayad dakhele '' bashad.
    🔹 `neqn -f filename` --> 📄 Hesab kardane expression az file.
    🔹 `neqn -n` --> 🔢 Be dast avardane natije ra faghat chap mikonad, bedune payam.

🛠 **Mesal-ha:**

    $ neqn '1 + 1'

    🔹 Natije hesabe 1 + 1 ra namayesh midahad.

    $ neqn 'sqrt(25)'

    🔹 Natije jazre 25 ra namayesh midahad.

✅ **Mesal sade:**

    $ neqn '2 * 3 + 4'

    🔹  In dastoor natije mohasebate 2 * 3 + 4 (ke barabar ast ba 10) ra chap mikonad.

===================================
📌 2. English Version
===================================

📖 **Description:**
    The `neqn` command is a mathematical equation processor in the terminal. You can use it to perform simple calculations.

⚙️ **Options:**
    🔹 `neqn 'expression'` --> ➕ Evaluates a mathematical expression. The expression should be inside ''.
    🔹 `neqn -f filename` --> 📄 Evaluates expressions from a file.
    🔹 `neqn -n` --> 🔢 Print only the result, without messages.

🛠 **Examples:**

    $ neqn '1 + 1'

    🔹 Displays the result of the calculation 1 + 1.

    $ neqn 'sqrt(25)'

    🔹 Displays the square root of 25.

✅ **Simple Example & Explanation:**

    $ neqn '2 * 3 + 4'

    🔹 This command prints the result of the calculation 2 * 3 + 4 (which equals 10).

